M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 distinctly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 138, 139
) 0.53 mm long, asymmetrical, strongly sclerotized. Median lobe with fairly large basal bulb and prominent, robust articular process. Apical process of median lobe tubular, with subapical ostium, conspicuously notched ventrally (lateral view). Parameres almost evenly wide posterior bases and curved, with very narrowly membranous inner margins. Internal sac with strongly sclerotized, simple flagellum; spines and scale-like structures absent. E t y m o l o g y: The species epithet is the name of one of Philippine languages.
